      "countAsQuest:1": 1,
      "desc:8": "You know, these long, straight things are somewhat reminding you of sticks. Maybe sticking them in the ground will allow them to support crop growth! The arrows even come with a pointy bit to stab with!\n\n[note]Make some cropsticks.[/note]\n\nFor the first crops, you have a few options. Well, more than a few. \n1. §6Mushrooms§r, from plague zombies. (Warning below)\n2. §6Eggplant§r, from eggs, from chickens that spawn on the now-attainable grass\n3. §6Witchery seeds§r, §6cotton§r, §6barley§r, §6wheat§r, §6carrots§r, and §6potatoes§r, if you get a hoe, and hoe the grass. Carrots and potatoes you actually get form zombies, but you can\u0027t plant them without a hoe anyway.\n\n[note]Note: Oak Bonsai has a deterministic mutation recipe in Wheat + Brown Mushrooms.[/note]\n\n[warn]Warning: Don\u0027t breed brown and red mushrooms to minimise outside pools, as they have a deterministic recipe together, and nothing will breed... ever. Mushrooms need a light level of 9 to grow, so if you do mutations during the day to remove the 1/3 spread chance as well, then you won\u0027t even get those. \n\nJust weeds. Using brown mushrroms OR red mushrooms is fine. None of the other crops have such limitations.[/warn]",
